#To load modules use commands as following once your prompt is ready. 

$ module avail -----> lists the available modules 
$ module load <module_name> ----> loading module
$ module unload <module_name> ----> unloading module 
$ module list ----> lists the module that are loaded 
$ module spider ---> it gives out the detailed list of modules so that you could go along
$ module spider <module_name> --> gives detailed information about the particular module
$ which <module_name> ---> shows the path and the actual installed version of R
# incase if you have loaded R 
$ R (and hit enter) 
# your will be directed to the R workspace and started working on R. 
# to quit use
> q() (it will ask whether you want to save the workspace) 
